    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "mempool: recalculate stale BIP68 lockpoints with mempool parents in removeForReorg",
    "user": {
      "login": "javierpmateos",
      "id": 189172017,
      "node_id": "U_kgDOC0aJMQ",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/189172017?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/javierpmateos",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javierpmateos/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "When a transaction with `nSequence=0` (BIP68 relative locktime 0) enters\r\nthe mempool with an unconfirmed parent, `CalculatePrevHeights` assigns\r\n`nCoinHeight=tip+1` and the resulting LockPoints are cached with\r\n`maxInputBlock=genesis`. After `invalidateblock` lowers the tip,\r\n`TestLockPointValidity` returns true for genesis (always on chain),\r\nso the stale cached lockpoints are reused. `CheckSequenceLocksAtTip`\r\nthen incorrectly determines the lock is not satisfied and removes\r\nthe transaction along with all its descendants.\r\n\r\nThe fix detects the genesis sentinel (`maxInputBlock->nHeight==0` with\r\n`lp.height>0`) in `filter_final_and_mature`, which indicates lockpoints\r\ncomputed with mempool parent inputs, and forces fresh recalculation via\r\n`CalculateLockPointsAtTip` instead of using the stale cache.\r\n\r\nAdded `mempool_reorg_bip68_stale_lockpoints.py` which verifies that\r\nboth BIP68-disabled and BIP68-enabled children with mempool parents\r\nsurvive a multi-block reorg via `invalidateblock`.\r\n\r\nReproducer for unpatched nodes:\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/javierpmateos/c55d365973adbf488a852dc5e0b77dec\r\n\r\nSame class of issue fixed for TRUC in #33504.\r\n\r\nCloses #35007",
