      "created_at": null,
      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/9dc0642ac58fd75993d8e5bfa5cecbbb0d5397a0",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "47912b881af0d6eb3697892ea391d879dfa2f749",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/47912b881af0d6eb3697892ea391d879dfa2f749"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 47912b881af0d6eb3697892ea391d879dfa2f749\nparent d868667fdc534c7ac04d4348c31a50e26679ef34\nauthor javierpmateos <javierpmateos@gmail.com> 1775592322 +0000\ncommitter javierpmateos <javierpmateos@gmail.com> 1775643448 +0000\n\nmempool: recalculate stale BIP68 lockpoints with mempool parents in removeForReorg\n\nWhen a transaction with nSequence=0 (BIP68 relative locktime 0) enters\nthe mempool with an unconfirmed parent, CalculatePrevHeights assigns\nnCoinHeight=tip+1 and the resulting LockPoints are cached with\nmaxInputBlock=genesis. After invalidateblock lowers the tip,\nTestLockPointValidity returns true for genesis (always on chain),\nso the stale cached lockpoints are reused. CheckSequenceLocksAtTip\nthen incorrectly determines the lock is not satisfied and removes\nthe transaction along with all its descendants.\n\nFix: in filter_final_and_mature, detect the genesis sentinel\n(maxInputBlock->nHeight==0 with lp.height>0) which indicates\nlockpoints computed with mempool parent inputs, and force fresh\nrecalculation via CalculateLockPointsAtTip.\n\nThis is the same class of issue fixed for TRUC in #33504.\n\nCloses #35007\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAggyoNBoWn+yM8C/RZK1EKr1LKNe\noXcJzLMx6IcjZigAAAAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQHYr/Uubf1YL1QWXKGNYzLX1iIvPsyYmrdrojJtTuzvN/dZxjsqiVKpLVkHXa3mP5i\nsGB1gC0hpEhXVv+5Pf5AY=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/d868667fdc534c7ac04d4348c31a50e26679ef34",
          "sha": "d868667fdc534c7ac04d4348c31a50e26679ef34",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/d868667fdc534c7ac04d4348c31a50e26679ef34"
        }
      ],
      "message": "mempool: recalculate stale BIP68 lockpoints with mempool parents in removeForReorg\n\nWhen a transaction with nSequence=0 (BIP68 relative locktime 0) enters\nthe mempool with an unconfirmed parent, CalculatePrevHeights assigns\nnCoinHeight=tip+1 and the resulting LockPoints are cached with\nmaxInputBlock=genesis. After invalidateblock lowers the tip,\nTestLockPointValidity returns true for genesis (always on chain),\nso the stale cached lockpoints are reused. CheckSequenceLocksAtTip\nthen incorrectly determines the lock is not satisfied and removes\nthe transaction along with all its descendants.\n\nFix: in filter_final_and_mature, detect the genesis sentinel\n(maxInputBlock->nHeight==0 with lp.height>0) which indicates\nlockpoints computed with mempool parent inputs, and force fresh\nrecalculation via CalculateLockPointsAtTip.\n\nThis is the same class of issue fixed for TRUC in #33504.\n\nCloses #35007",
